<td width=3D"514" height=3D"309">
<h1 align=3D"center"> Weightlessness</h1>
 <p>  While the actual <a href=3D"http://hyperphysics.phy-astr.gsu.edu/hbas=
e/mass.html#wgt">weight</a> of a person is determined by his <a href=3D"htt=
p://hyperphysics.phy-astr.gsu.edu/hbase/mass.html#mas">mass</a> and the acc=
eleration of gravity, one's "perceived weight" or "effective weight" comes =
from the fact that he is supported by floor, chair, etc. If all support is =
removed suddenly and the person begins to fall freely, he feels suddenly "w=
eightless" - so weightlessness refers to a state of being in free fall in w=
hich there is no perceived support. The state of weightlessness can be achi=
eved in several ways, all of which involve significant physical principles.=
</p><br>
